Also, Node.js does not have a direct equivalent to Python's `os.startfile()`, so we use `cross-spawn` to achieve the same effect.

Please note that this code will not work in a browser environment, as it requires Node.js. Also, the code assumes that the file is a Windows executable (.exe). If this is not the case, you would need to adjust the code accordingly.

Finally, the `https.get()` function is used instead of `requests.get()` as Node.js does not have a built-in module for HTTP requests. The `https` module is used for HTTPS requests.

